Instructions for running/testing program on Debian/Ubuntu distros

Install node.js:

  curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | sudo -E bash -
  sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

While in the project directory run 'npm install' to install dependencies

While in the project directory run 'npm start' to run program

Navigate to 'localhost:3000' to access the app for testing

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Application written using node.js using the express.js generator to create the
skeleton of the app. JQuery AJAX library used for communication between the
front and back ends. Bootstrap used for front end.

Application is currently hosted on a Digital Ocean server running nginx at: 
  http://http://138.68.234.229/

Heavy lifting and application core is in routes/roll.js
